         <abstract>
            <p>We consider matrices of the following form: G&lt;sub&gt;n&lt;/sub&gt;(a&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt;, a&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt;,⋯, a&lt;sub&gt;n - 1&lt;/sub&gt;, b&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt;, b&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt;,⋯, b&lt;sub&gt;n&lt;/sub&gt;) = (β&lt;sub&gt;i,j&lt;/sub&gt;), 1 ≤ i, j ≤ n, where a&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt;,⋯, a&lt;sub&gt;n - 1&lt;/sub&gt;, b&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt;,⋯, b&lt;sub&gt;n&lt;/sub&gt; are constants and &lt;tex-math&gt;$\beta_{i,j} = b_j, \quad j \geqq i; \quad \beta_{ij} = a_j, \quad j &lt; i$&lt;/tex-math&gt;. We deduce in analytic form the determinant, inverse matrix, characteristic equation, and eigenvectors of G&lt;sub&gt;n&lt;/sub&gt;. Knowing these properties enables us to generate valuable test matrices by appropriately selecting the order and elements of G&lt;sub&gt;n&lt;/sub&gt;.</p>
